author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: Commerce suffers 35-14 defeat to Prince Avenue
text:
Saturday October 3rd, 2015 9:09AM 6:10AM ( 1 day ago ) Weather Alert Posted 7:03AM on Saturday 3rd October 2015 ( 2 hours ago ) Commerce suffers 35-14 defeat to Prince Avenue By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 6: Playoff, region races shaping up after big night VIDEO: Gainesville makes most of six Salem turnovers to set up Lanier showdown 
COMMERCE — Commerce could not overcome Prince Avenue Christian on Friday, falling 35-14 in Commerce. 
The Tigers (3-3, 2-2 Region 8-A) put up 217 yards of offense, including 70 yards rushing for Cole Chancey and 57 yards for Caleb Brooks. But the Wolverines put up 286 yards and jumped out to a 21-0 first half lead. 
Brooks scored on a four-yard run to make it 21-7 in the second quarter, but Prince Avenue responded with a 47-yard touchdown run to lead 28-7 at the interval. 
Brooks hooked up with J'Varius Wood on a 20-yard touchdown pass in the third quarter, but Prince Avenue fired right back to maintain a three-touchdown cushion. 
Commerce will take a bye next week before taking on Providence Christian on Oct. 16. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Commerce football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
